text: Kyle McDuffie is a Canadian former long jumper who won a bronze medal at the 1986 Commonwealth Games in Edinburgh, Scotland. McDuffie won the Canadian national championships in 1985 and 1987. ==References== Category:Year of birth missing (living people) Category:Living people Category:Canadian male long jumpers Category:Athletes (track and field) at the 1986 Commonwealth Games Category:Commonwealth Games medallists in athletics Category:Commonwealth Games bronze medallists for Canada
